    "description": "<p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >What Tower of Jank offers:</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Unique card combat</strong></p><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >There's 2 classes with over 70 cards each. Most of these cards have synergies some of which even I as a developer have not found yet.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Relics that increase the build variety even further.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Before every run you can take one or more pills that will change how you approach making your build.</p></li></ul></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Play how you want</strong></p><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >You can use cards by yourself in real time. </p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >You can <strong>stop time</strong>.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >You can make it so the <strong>cards are played automatically</strong> and focus on dodging and building the deck.</p></li></ul></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Difficulty</strong> - the game is hard. You have to break the game or the game breaks you.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p></li></ul><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > </p>",
